		<credit project="CfPBoK@https://slebok.github.io/cfpbok/"/>
		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014"></a><br><code>sle2014/paper02</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>A SAT-Based Debugging Tool for State Machines and Sequence Diagrams</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/PetraRadeljakKaufmann.html">Petra Radeljak Kaufmann</a>, <a href="../profile/MartinKronegger.html">Martin Kronegger</a>, <a href="../profile/AndreasPfandler.html">Andreas Pfandler</a>, <a href="../profile/MartinaSeidl.html">Martina Seidl</a>, <a href="../profile/MagdalenaWidl.html">Magdalena Widl</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_2">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_2</a></li>
<li>Original shorter version of <a href="../sle2014s/paper04.html"><em>Intra- and interdiagram consistency checking of behavioral multiview models</em></a> (SLE 2014 SI)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It encodes consistency/debugging of behavioral models as a SAT problem to find witnesses/counterexamples.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The contribution includes an implemented debugging tool integrated with EMF-based modeling.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagL">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It reasons about the executable behavior of state machines and their interaction scenarios.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5c.html"><span class="tagL">T5C: Testing</span></a><ul><li> It employs grammar-based whitebox fuzzing as part of the evaluation/testing of the approach.
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
		<footer/>
